# 3-Phase Motor Forward & Reverse Control (PLC - TIA Portal)

## Project Description
This project demonstrates the control of a 3-phase asynchronous motor in both forward and reverse directions using Siemens S7-1200 PLC (TIA Portal).

The system includes:
- Multiple start buttons
- Stop button (NC)
- Thermal relay protection (NC)
- Electrical interlocking
- Self-holding (latching)

---

## System Logic

### Forward Operation
The forward motor starts when:
- Thermal relay is healthy (NC contact closed)
- Stop button is not pressed (NC contact closed)
- Forward start button is pressed
- Reverse motor is NOT active (interlock)

The system uses a self-holding contact to keep the motor running after the start button is released.

---

### Reverse Operation
The reverse motor starts when:
- Thermal relay is healthy (NC contact closed)
- Stop button is not pressed (NC contact closed)
- Reverse start button is pressed
- Forward motor is NOT active (interlock)

Electrical interlocking prevents both directions from running at the same time.

---

## Safety Features

- Thermal Relay Protection (NC)
- Stop Button (NC)
- Electrical Interlock (Forward ↔ Reverse)
- Self-holding (latch logic)

NOTE:
In real industrial applications, mechanical interlocking between contactors MUST be used in addition to PLC logic.

---

## I/O Configuration

| Tag Name           | Address | Type | Description              |
|-------------------|--------|------|--------------------------|
| I_THERMAL_RELAY   | I0.0   | Bool | Thermal relay (NC)       |
| I_START_BTN_1     | I0.1   | Bool | Forward start button     |
| I_STOP_BTN        | I0.2   | Bool | Stop button (NC)         |
| I_FORWARD_BTN     | I0.3   | Bool | Forward command          |
| I_RESERVE_BTN     | I0.4   | Bool | Reverse command          |
| I_START_BTN_2     | I0.5   | Bool | Reverse start button     |
| Q_FORWARD_MOTOR   | Q0.0   | Bool | Forward motor output     |
| Q_RESERVE_MOTOR   | Q0.1   | Bool | Reverse motor output     |

---

## Technologies Used

- Siemens TIA Portal
- S7-1200 PLC (CPU 1212C DC/DC/DC)
- Ladder Logic (LAD)

---

## How to Run

1. Open the project in TIA Portal
2. Configure the PLC (CPU 1212C)
3. Download to PLC or run with PLCSIM
4. Monitor inputs/outputs
5. Test forward and reverse operations

---

## Key Learning Outcomes

- Forward / Reverse motor control
- Electrical interlocking
- Self-holding (latching)
- Industrial safety basics
- PLC ladder programming

---

## Important Note

This project is for educational purposes.

For real industrial systems:
- Mechanical interlocking is required
- Proper protection circuits must be used
- Emergency stop circuits must be implemented correctly

